  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (fidelity gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The CFD model employs a simplified laminar-flow assumption and omits turbulence-induced shear stress contributions, which are physically present in the real pump at high rotational speeds. No validation activity tests the impact of this turbulence exclusion on hemolysis index predictions.",
