      "rationale": "The CFD model employs a steady-state laminar Navier-Stokes formulation with the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model. Turbulence is excluded on the basis that the nominal operating point Reynolds number in the volute is approximately 2100, near the laminar-turbulent transition boundary. Model form is documented as a simplified laminar model. No fidelity trade study quantifying the impact of turbulence exclusion on hemolysis index was performed, and no validation result tests this abstraction."
